%%{ init: { 'theme': 'base', 'sequence': { 'mirrorActors': false } } }%%

sequenceDiagram
    actor U as AI Engineer
    participant Cat as MCP Catalog
    participant Op as Lifecycle Operator
    participant S as MCP Server
    participant GW as MCP Gateway
    participant KC as Keycloak
    participant AU as Authorino
    participant P as Gen AI Studio
    participant LS as Llama Stack
    participant LLM as vLLM

    Note over U,LLM: Phase 1 — Discover & Deploy

    U->>Cat: Browse available MCP servers
    Cat-->>U: Server list (capabilities, transport, metadata)
    U->>Cat: Select server to deploy
    Cat->>Op: Deploy request
    Op->>S: Deploy server on OpenShift
    Op->>GW: Register server with gateway
    GW-->>Op: Registration confirmed

    Note over U,LLM: Phase 2 — Authenticate

    U->>KC: Authenticate (obtain JWT)
    KC-->>U: Access token (roles: mcp-user, mcp-admin)

    Note over U,LLM: Phase 3 — Consume via Gen AI Studio

    U->>P: "What pods are running?"
    P->>LS: Chat request + available tools
    LS->>LLM: Inference request (prompt + tool definitions)
    LLM-->>LS: Tool call: pods_list_in_namespace

    Note over U,LLM: Phase 4 — Gateway Routes Tool Call

    LS->>GW: MCP tools/call (Bearer token)
    GW->>AU: Auth check (JWT)
    AU->>KC: Validate token + roles
    KC-->>AU: Valid
    AU-->>GW: Authorized
    GW->>S: Dispatch tool call
    S-->>GW: Tool result
    GW-->>LS: Tool result

    Note over U,LLM: Phase 5 — AI Responds

    LS->>LLM: Tool result + original prompt
    LLM-->>LS: Natural language response
    LS-->>P: Response
    P-->>U: "There are 5 pods running..."
